The paper deals with interference mitigation in 5G cellular systems, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of massive MIMO and heterogeneous networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a practical solution for the design problem, which may also make it relevant to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
